N2  - Two groups of managers involved in a cognitive-oriented training program were studied. The structured or directive style was found to be more effective in achieving group cohesiveness, minimizing participant conflict, increasing communication, achieving group productivity, and encouraging a favorable attitude toward the trainer than was a less structured trainer style.
