T1  - The Relation of Group Performance to the Age of Members in Homogeneous Groups
AU  - Webber, Ross A.
Y1  - 1974/09/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254660
DO  - 10.5465/254660
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 570
EP  - 574
VL  - 17
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the findings of a study on the relation of a homogeneous group's performance to the age of its members. The study asked four hundred individuals and 80 five-person groups from management development programs and university classes to complete two 25-item vocabulary synonym exercises. Group score was found to be positively associated with the prior performance of group members on the individual exercise. Research also suggests that younger groups are less competitive and hence more cooperative in group settings.
AB  - The article discusses the findings of a study on the relation of a homogeneous group's performance to the age of its members. The study asked four hundred individuals and 80 five-person groups from management development programs and university classes to complete two 25-item vocabulary synonym exercises. Group score was found to be positively associated with the prior performance of group members on the individual exercise. Research also suggests that younger groups are less competitive and hence more cooperative in group settings.
