PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article compares the attitudes and behaviors of African Americans and white supervisors in the U.S. Data concerning leader behavior was collected with simulated work groups using the one-way mirror technique. Twelve black and twelve white undergraduate students were selected to assume supervisory roles and supervise three different racially mixed groups of subordinates. The author notes that a scarcity of black supervisors has lead to a lack of adequate research on the subject. It is noted that the adoption of a no difference belief could contribute to increased racial harmony and group effectiveness.
